{"title":"pip User Guide","date":"2018-02-28T03:55:30.000Z","date_formatted":{"ll":"Feb 27, 2018","L":"02/27/2018","MM-DD":"02-27"},"link":"post/package control","tags":["Package control","Python"],"categories":["Python"],"updated":"2020-05-10T23:09:10.000Z","content":"<p>This post is a collection of required commands to manage the packages. From cradle to grave, for a package, it will experience several stages:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<ul><li>Installation</li>\n<li>Check status</li>\n<li>Upgrade</li>\n<li>Uninstallation</li>\n</ul></blockquote>\n<p>Thus, following sections follow the order of these procedures.</p>\n<a id=\"more\"></a><h1 id=\"install-packages\">Install Packages<a href=\"#install-packages\" title=\"Install Packages\"></a></h1><h2 id=\"common-use\">Common Use<a href=\"#common-use\" title=\"Common Use\"></a></h2><figure class=\"highlight bash\"><table><tr><td class=\"gutter\"><pre><span class=\"line\">1</span><br></pre></td><td class=\"code\"><pre><span class=\"line\">$ pip install &lt;package-name&gt;</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure><h2 id=\"install-a-batch-of-packages\">Install a batch of packages<a href=\"#install-a-batch-of-packages\" title=\"Install a batch of packages\"></a></h2><p>Sometimes it is quite annoying to install require packages one by one. </p>\n<figure class=\"highlight bash\"><table><tr><td class=\"gutter\"><pre><span class=\"line\">1</span><br></pre></td><td class=\"code\"><pre><span class=\"line\">$ pip install -r &lt;required-pakages.txt&gt;</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure><h2 id=\"upgrade-packages\">Upgrade Packages<a href=\"#upgrade-packages\" title=\"Upgrade Packages\"></a></h2><figure class=\"highlight bash\"><table><tr><td class=\"gutter\"><pre><span class=\"line\">1</span><br></pre></td><td class=\"code\"><pre><span class=\"line\">$ pip install --upgrade &lt;package-name&gt;</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure><h1 id=\"check-packages\">Check Packages<a href=\"#check-packages\" title=\"Check Packages\"></a></h1><h2 id=\"an-overview-of-all-packages\">An overview of all packages<a href=\"#an-overview-of-all-packages\" title=\"An overview of all packages\"></a></h2><figure class=\"highlight bash\"><table><tr><td class=\"gutter\"><pre><span class=\"line\">1</span><br><span class=\"line\">2</span><br><span class=\"line\">3</span><br><span class=\"line\">4</span><br><span class=\"line\">5</span><br></pre></td><td class=\"code\"><pre><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"comment\"># list all packages</span></span><br><span class=\"line\">$ pip list </span><br><span class=\"line\"></span><br><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"comment\"># list the packages need upgrading</span></span><br><span class=\"line\">$ pip list --outdated</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure><h2 id=\"information-of-one-specified-packages\">Information of one specified packages<a href=\"#information-of-one-specified-packages\" title=\"Information of one specified packages\"></a></h2><figure class=\"highlight bash\"><table><tr><td class=\"gutter\"><pre><span class=\"line\">1</span><br><span class=\"line\">2</span><br><span class=\"line\">3</span><br><span class=\"line\">4</span><br><span class=\"line\">5</span><br></pre></td><td class=\"code\"><pre><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"comment\"># show the detail about a specified package</span></span><br><span class=\"line\">$ pip show &lt;package-name&gt; ...</span><br><span class=\"line\"></span><br><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"comment\"># Show the full list of installed files for each package.</span></span><br><span class=\"line\">$ pip show -f &lt;package-name&gt;</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure><h1 id=\"uninstall-packages\">Uninstall Packages<a href=\"#uninstall-packages\" title=\"Uninstall Packages\"></a></h1><figure class=\"highlight bash\"><table><tr><td class=\"gutter\"><pre><span class=\"line\">1</span><br></pre></td><td class=\"code\"><pre><span class=\"line\">$ pip uninstall &lt;package-name&gt;</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure><h1 id=\"reference\">Reference<a href=\"#reference\" title=\"Reference\"></a></h1><ul><li><a href=\"https://pip.pypa.io/en/stable/user_guide/#installing-packages\" target=\"_blank\">pip Official Guide</a></li>\n</ul>","prev":{"title":"统计学习基本概念（2）","link":"post/统计学习概论2"},"next":{"title":"统计学习基本概念（1）","link":"post/统计学习概论"},"plink":"https://magi003769.github.io/post/package control/","toc":[{"id":"install-packages","title":"Install Packages","index":"1","children":[{"id":"common-use","title":"Common Use","index":"1.1"},{"id":"install-a-batch-of-packages","title":"Install a batch of packages","index":"1.2"},{"id":"upgrade-packages","title":"Upgrade Packages","index":"1.3"}]},{"id":"check-packages","title":"Check Packages","index":"2","children":[{"id":"an-overview-of-all-packages","title":"An overview of all packages","index":"2.1"},{"id":"information-of-one-specified-packages","title":"Information of one specified packages","index":"2.2"}]},{"id":"uninstall-packages","title":"Uninstall Packages","index":"3"},{"id":"reference","title":"Reference","index":"4"}]}